trans-unit.source: 📌 Founded in the vibrant currents of music and entrepreneurial spirit, VCG Recordz's journey began in 2013 when a young Kitsui, at the tender age of 13, started dabbling in music production. His passion quickly escalated as he explored various recording and music composition software, including Cubase, Logic Pro X, FL Studio, and Reaper.

📌 The year 2018 marked a significant turning point when Kitsui met Køni and shortly thereafter, Biggy. By 2019, Kitsui and Køni were not just acquaintances but collaborators, bonding over their shared love for music, rapping, and singing together. Kitsui, who had honed his skills in voice mixing, took under his wing the task of mixing both his and Køni’s vocals. This dynamic duo spent countless hours—days, weeks, and months—creating music, especially during the 2020 Covid-19 lockdowns, always with Biggy by their side.

📌 As their skills sharpened, Kitsui passed on his knowledge of mixing to Køni, empowering him to record autonomously and master his vocal finesse using professional plugins and custom presets. This led to an influx of requests from other artists seeking their mixing magic, but without a formal structure, they were initially unable to take on external projects.

📌 Realizing the potential, and driven by a staunch determination to remain independent, the idea of forming their own label took root. In 2021, conversations began to shape this vision, culminating in the official launch of VCG Recordz on January 16, 2024.

📌 At the helm of the company stood Kitsui, Køni, and Biggy, with Biggy honored as the president for his unwavering support and solidarity from the very start—not just in music but in life and business endeavors. Despite Biggy’s title, Kitsui manages the day-to-day operations, including finances, accounting, web development, and client management, while Køni and he jointly steers the business decisions.

📌 Biggy also ventured into videography, having filmed all their amateur music videos since 2019 and starring in their first official music video in 2022. The label grew to include beatmakers like Oddgyes first, then Shidozz and DMB, expanding their reach and influence in the music industry. VCG Recordz also launched VCG Production, a platform on YouTube and Beatstars showcasing and selling beats crafted by their talented team.

📌 Today, VCG Recordz stands as a hub for artists seeking to collaborate and innovate within the music industry. Operating from two home studios, the label not only produces and mixes their own material but also extends these services to a wide array of local and national artists, steadfastly supporting a vision of creativity, independence, and collective artistic effort.
Kitsui & Køni are a duo of French rappers. Together, they have released over 30 songs, including 4 EPs, and have recorded more than 150 tracks along 8 years of activity.
MADPOOF is a Trap, Drum & Bass and new-age Breakcore producer. He has released more than 10 singles already.
Loupa is a French rapper known for his global perspective. He travels around the world to work with artists from abroad, bringing diverse influences to his music.
Cl6ud6 is a French rapper who has underground and modern vibes. He has collaborated with Køni numerous times.

Gaxve, a producer from Spain, Europe, primarily focused on new-age Breakcore, Drum & Bass, and Jungle, collaborated with MADPOOF on the tracks "Refresh Token" and "Internal Conflict", released via Breakstation.
CXMET is a phonkwave producer who collaborated with MADPOOF on the track "EYES OF HEAVEN", released via Breakstation.

We help emerging artists distribute their music on all major streaming and download platforms. We offer two flexible options: a pay-as-you-go plan, where artists pay a flat fee per single or project (up to 12 releases per year), or an unlimited monthly subscription allowing unlimited releases. Subscription artists become part of the VCG family and are showcased on our website.

Beatmakers can distribute their work through our network, on platforms like BeatStars, and also on our YouTube channel, at no cost. Join our growing community and have your profile showcased on the VCG website. It is also an opportunity to connect to our artists and producers network. Our goal is to federate a strong community of beatmakers.

We offer quality recording and mixing services specializing in hip-hop/rap music, with plans to expand to other genres. Based in Haute-Savoie, France, we operate amateur studios. Artists can utilize our services independently or combine them with distribution for maximum reach. We plan to invest in a professional studio in the future.
